<!--Hand 01 24 top left--><!--hand 02 64760 top right-->
<lb/><p rend="right"><placeName>50 Albemarle <choice><abbr>St.</abbr><expan>Street</expan></choice></placeName></p>
<lb/><p rend="right">26<hi rend="sup"><hi rend="underline">th</hi></hi><choice><abbr>Jan<hi rend="sup">y.</hi></abbr><expan>January</expan></choice></p>
<lb/><p rend="right">1858</p>
<lb/><p>My Dear <persName>Madam</persName></p>
<lb/><p>I know <persName>M<hi rend="sup">r</hi>
<lb/>Taylor</persName> very well 
<lb/>and the circumstance 
<lb/>also which induced 
<lb/>him to write to <persName>the 
<lb/>Admiral</persName>. A <persName>M<hi rend="sup"><hi rend="underline">rs</hi></hi>
<lb/>Bevan</persName>, wife of 
<lb/>a London banker 
<lb/>wished to present 

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_001192_0002"/><!--pb/@n='2'--> 
<lb/>me with something 
<lb/>and as <persName>M<hi rend="sup"><hi rend="underline">r</hi></hi> Taylor</persName>
<lb/>thought that this 
<lb/>meant something 
<lb/>handsome I mentioned 
<lb/>the instrument. But 
<lb/>as this was more 
<lb/>than two months 
<lb/>ago I suspect that 
<lb/>he was too sanguine 
<lb/>in his expectations 
<lb/>for I have heard 
<lb/>nothing more of 
<lb/>it from him since 
<lb/>I shall see him 

	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_001192_0003"/><!--pb/@n='3'--> 
<lb/>in a day or two and 
<lb/>then proceed to get 
<lb/>the instrument for 
<lb/>myself. &amp; I should 
<lb/>like to know if they 
<lb/>are to be had in 
<lb/>London &amp; where 
<lb/>I dont like to be 
<lb/>troublesome and 
<lb/>hope you will excuse 
<lb/>this</p>
<lb/><p rend="right">I am Yours Truly</p>
<lb/><p rend="center">David Livingstone</p>
<lb/><p rend="center"><persName>M<hi rend="sup">rs</hi>. A. <choice><sic>Smythe</sic><corr>Smyth</corr></choice></persName>.</p>
			
